          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1615470589538-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cauliflower stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>cauliflower head<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>into small florets</p><p>Add 200g <span class=\"text-danger\">[400g]</span> of <strong>cauliflower florets </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!) to the pot with the <strong>conchiglie</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until everything is cooked through and tender</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside in the colander</p><p>Reserve the pot for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1615470566386-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
