            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>veg stock</strong> with 200g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400g] </span>of the <strong>reserved</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>cauliflower stalks </strong>and <strong>florets </strong>to the pot and cook for 8-10 min until softened</p><p>Tip: Roast any remaining cauliflower with some spices for a tasty snack!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
